At some point in the small hours she?s separated from Charles and doesn?t know how many pills she?s taken. All alone in the crowd she watches benevolently from the corner. There, by the righthand speaker, is one of the Wallies from the bar, apparently unseeing, dancing, as they say, for himself, fascinated by this bespectacled, red-and-black-striped figure in the shadow, and she approaches, drawn.